parent_disease: Acute Myocardial Infarction / Post-Cardiac Intervention Complications
reasoning: Stunned myocardium occurs as a complication in 20-50% of acute coronary syndrome cases and cardiac interventions. Global incidence estimate ~8.5 per 100k based on post-MI incidence of ~20-25 per 100k and 30-40% complication rate. Data from cardiology registries and interventional studies.
